lgfx-bus-rgb-rs
================

This crate is a derivative work of LovyanGFX
(https://github.com/lovyan03/LovyanGFX), specifically the file

  src/lgfx/v1/platforms/esp32s3/Bus_RGB.cpp
  src/lgfx/v1/platforms/esp32s3/Bus_RGB.hpp

Upstream LovyanGFX is copyright (c) lovyan03 and contributors (ciniml,
mongonta0716, tobozo), and is distributed under the BSD-3-Clause
("FreeBSD") license. See:

  https://github.com/lovyan03/LovyanGFX/blob/master/license.txt

The Rust port (this crate) adds the following on top of LovyanGFX's
work:

  - Adaptation to esp-hal 1.0 (Rust no_std) primitives, where the
    LovyanGFX C++ uses raw IDF / soc-struct register access.
  - Use of esp-alloc capability-tagged heap regions in place of
    `heap_caps_malloc(MALLOC_CAP_SPIRAM)` and
    `heap_caps_malloc(MALLOC_CAP_DMA)`.
  - Rust ownership / borrowing discipline around the singleton
    descriptor storage.

